In 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish toss together pears, cranberries, 2 tablespoons of the brown sugar, 2 tablespoons of the whole wheat flour, ginger, cinnamon and vanilla. In small bowl combine remaining brown sugar, remaining whole wheat flour and KELLOGG'S SPECIAL K Vanilla Almond cereal. Drizzle with butter. Mix until combined. Sprinkle over fruit mixture. Bake at 375 degrees F for 25 minutes or until fruit is tender. Serve warm with scoops of frozen yogurt, if desired.